  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6586 sitting between the major negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4498M) and positive gamma wall at 6600 (+4725M), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but biased toward selling any push higher into the 6600 resistance zone. The PIN regime with 3526M total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively sell rallies above 6600 and buy dips below 6500, creating a tight trading range with mean reversion tendencies. The gex_surge event combined with the -45% 1-min change indicates recent volatility expansion, but the strong positive gamma at 6600/6605 should cap upside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to chop between 6500-6600 with limited breakout potential.",
